default&#xa0;
defaultDisability and Community Care Law
defaultCommunity Care is a specialised niche area of law w
defaulthich on many occasions can require oral permission hearings just so that the judge can understand the area and the surrounding legislation. It is an area w
defaulth
defaultere many of those affected by the decisions of local authorities do not get access to advocacy
default or re
defaultpresentation
default and so never receive adequate care. The ombudsman has no power to enforce any action and even to get a determination would usually require a lawyer just to make sense of a situation. We find time after time that local authorities are enacting 
defaultpolicies across the board which are unlawful and there is no way to challenge and force a change except via judicial review. 
defaultAs noted above, we provide free telephone advice given by solicitors to the members of the public with community care problems. 
defaultDue to the nature of the area of law, almost every issue concerns a person with a disability. We have found that the number of telephone calls have been increasing as Local Authorities have had their budgets reduced. This has led to those with disabilities
default having their care reduced unlawfully and any changes can only increase this size of the problem. There has been no conside
defaultration of the effects of such 
defaultproposed changes on those with disabilities. We would request that if there is any doubt as to the natu
defaultre of the effects on those with disabilities or the levels of problems that they are facing then we would invite anyone from the committee or from the Ministry of Justice to come and listen to our advice lines. 
defaultThis is an open invitation.default&#xa0;
